UNITED STATES ex rel. Emily FUNICELLI, a friend of Bruno Fedeli, Relator Appellant, v. Henry H. CURRAN, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, Respondent Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 19, 1926.) No. 311. A. P. Ruffalo, of New York City, for appellant. Emory R. Buckner, of New York City (Charles L. Sylvester, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
